# Django REST Framework - ModelViewSet Overview

## 1. Built-in ACTION METHODS (automatic endpoints)

These correspond to HTTP endpoints:

- `list()` → GET /tasks/
- `retrieve()` → GET /tasks/1/
- `create()` → POST /tasks/
- `update()` → PUT /tasks/1/
- `partial_update()` → PATCH /tasks/1/
- `destroy()` → DELETE /tasks/1/

👉 You can override any of these methods.

---

## 2. HOOK METHODS (for customization)

Used to modify logic without rewriting full action methods:

- `perform_create(self, serializer)`
- `perform_update(self, serializer)`
- `perform_destroy(self, instance)`

👉 Recommended way to inject business logic.

---

## 3. QUERY / OBJECT METHODS

Control what data is fetched:

- `get_queryset()`
- `get_object()`
- `filter_queryset(queryset)`

---

## 4. SERIALIZER METHODS

Control how serializers are used:

- `get_serializer()`
- `get_serializer_class()`
- `get_serializer_context()`

---

## 5. PERMISSION / AUTH METHODS

Dynamic control over access:

- `get_permissions()`
- `get_authenticators()`
- `get_throttles()`

---

## 6. PAGINATION METHODS

Used internally for pagination:

- `paginate_queryset(queryset)`
- `get_paginated_response(data)`

---

## 7. CONFIGURABLE ATTRIBUTES (class-level)

These are commonly defined in your ViewSet:

- `queryset`
- `serializer_class`
- `pagination_class`
- `permission_classes`
- `authentication_classes`
- `filter_backends`
- `throttle_classes`
- `parser_classes`
- `renderer_classes`
- `lookup_field`
- `lookup_url_kwarg`

